  "prompt": "What does \"RIC\" mean with reference to email?",
  "response": "In the context of email, \"RIC\" typically stands for \"Reply in Chain.\" It refers to the practice of replying to an email while keeping the original message and any previous replies intact in the thread. This helps maintain the context of the conversation and allows recipients to easily follow the discussion. However, it's worth noting that acronyms can have different meanings in different contexts, so it's always good to consider the specific usage.",
